The course gives an overview of children's literature theory and the developmental history of Estonian children's literature and journalism. A selection of the most prominent texts in Estonian children's literature is introduced via lectures, seminars and independent work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) get acquainted with the basic concepts of children's literature theory; 2) to teach to understand the specifics of children's literature; 3) to get acquainted with the development stages of children's literature, the most important Estonian children's writers and works.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows the specifics of children's literature; 2) knows the development stages of Estonian children's literature and the most important Estonian children's writers; 3) is familiar with contemporary Estonian children's literature; 4) is familiar with contemporary Estonian children's press; 5) knows how to stimulate reading in children and to use children's literature in the teacher's daily work.
